WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:center
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:00.270 --> 00:00:03.140
Open up the borderless map, then

3
00:00:03.140 --> 00:00:06.340
Head for that unknown edge of the ocean

4
00:00:06.340 --> 00:00:10.730
LET’S SAIL ON right now, hoist your sails up high

5
00:00:10.730 --> 00:00:13.720
Riding on the wind

6
00:00:18.850 --> 00:00:23.060
DON’T GIVE UP, it’s time to finish what we started

7
00:00:23.250 --> 00:00:26.030
So don't you grow disheartened

8
00:00:26.340 --> 00:00:29.790
Laugh the tears away through the storm

9
00:00:29.990 --> 00:00:34.220
SHOUT IT OUT, when you feel down always remember

10
00:00:34.560 --> 00:00:36.820
That’s what your friends are there for

11
00:00:36.850 --> 00:00:38.980
Y’know there’s no point in fronting,

12
00:00:38.980 --> 00:00:42.900
your crew will always have your back

13
00:00:43.270 --> 00:00:47.000
Even in the face of utter darkness

14
00:00:47.230 --> 00:00:49.990
C’mon, BRAVE IT OUT We’ll be alright

15
00:00:50.290 --> 00:00:53.780
Together you know that we’ll never lose a fight

16
00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:56.770
Open up the borderless map, then

17
00:00:56.790 --> 00:00:59.630
Head for that unknown edge of the ocean

18
00:00:59.930 --> 00:01:04.210
All great journeys starts with a single step

19
00:01:04.280 --> 00:01:05.220
DREAMIN’ ON

20
00:01:05.220 --> 00:01:08.000
Open up the borderless map, then

21
00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:10.740
Raise the flag we swore to defend

22
00:01:10.890 --> 00:01:13.630
We’ll never stop until we’ve reached the top

23
00:01:13.700 --> 00:01:18.100
Just be true to yourself until the end

24
00:01:18.230 --> 00:01:22.940
Set sail and grab it, DREAMIN ON

25
00:01:32.950 --> 00:01:36.700
Within a vast, verdant forest...

26
00:01:37.990 --> 00:01:43.500
through lush flowers, brush, and trees,
a fresh and clear stream flows...

27
00:01:44.580 --> 00:01:47.590
into a picturesque sea.

28
00:01:48.760 --> 00:01:55.220
This story takes place in a Wano
still teeming with life.

29
00:01:56.670 --> 00:01:59.590
<b>Teahouse</b>

30
00:01:56.680 --> 00:01:59.600
You outran a moving mountain?!

31
00:01:59.600 --> 00:02:01.100
That's right!

32
00:02:01.100 --> 00:02:03.140
It was growling.

33
00:02:03.690 --> 00:02:05.310
Maybe...

34
00:02:05.310 --> 00:02:08.230
something angered the Mountain God!

35
00:02:10.150 --> 00:02:11.610
Just kidding!

36
00:02:11.610 --> 00:02:14.820
Anyway, you guys are all smiles.

37
00:02:14.820 --> 00:02:16.490
What happened?

38
00:02:15.030 --> 00:02:19.660
<b>Miss Tsuru,

Waitress



Teahouse

in the

Mountains</b>

39
00:02:16.490 --> 00:02:19.660
We finally caught one!

40
00:02:28.250 --> 00:02:30.130
What a lovely boar!

41
00:02:30.550 --> 00:02:34.220
We could get a platinum
if we took it to the capital!

42
00:02:34.220 --> 00:02:35.390
What?!

43
00:02:36.050 --> 00:02:38.260
That's enough to build a fine house!

44
00:02:38.600 --> 00:02:39.680
Yeah!

45
00:02:39.680 --> 00:02:44.480
The Kurokoma boss is looking for a legendary
white boar to display in his storefront,

46
00:02:44.890 --> 00:02:47.270
so he posted a reward for one.

47
00:02:47.270 --> 00:02:49.440
He can't put it on display!

48
00:02:49.820 --> 00:02:53.110
White boars are divine messengers.

49
00:02:58.160 --> 00:02:59.700
Kin'emon!

50
00:02:59.700 --> 00:03:01.490
Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow!

51
00:03:01.490 --> 00:03:04.540
You're stealing from my store again!

52
00:03:01.700 --> 00:03:08.080
<b>Kin'emon

Local Thug</b>

53
00:03:04.540 --> 00:03:08.080
C'mon, Miss Tsuru! You've
known me since we were kids!

54
00:03:08.500 --> 00:03:11.130
I'm like a brother who needs money!

55
00:03:11.130 --> 00:03:13.300
Yeah, because you gamble!

56
00:03:13.300 --> 00:03:16.840
Do you know how much you owe me?!

57
00:03:20.300 --> 00:03:24.140
The next time you try
and lay your hands on my money,

58
00:03:24.480 --> 00:03:27.810
I'll sell your organs!

59
00:03:29.230 --> 00:03:32.980
If you can't pay me back,
I'll settle for your clothes!

60
00:03:33.820 --> 00:03:39.530
<b>The Day of the Mountain God</b>

61
00:03:39.530 --> 00:03:42.450
Grandpa Katsuzo!
<b>Katsuzo</b>

62
00:03:42.450 --> 00:03:45.830
Ahh... Don't cry! Oh, wait...

63
00:03:42.660 --> 00:03:45.830
<b>Crematorium

Flower
Capital</b>

64
00:03:45.830 --> 00:03:49.170
I guess you can cry at a funeral.

65
00:03:49.170 --> 00:03:50.420
What's the matter?

66
00:03:50.880 --> 00:03:56.380
We finished the cremation
and were about to gather his bones,

67
00:03:56.380 --> 00:03:58.050
but then that man...!

68
00:03:58.050 --> 00:04:03.060
He started cooking oden
using my father's pyre!

69
00:04:08.440 --> 00:04:12.060
It seems like Lord Oden
is completely incapable of sailing.

70
00:04:12.520 --> 00:04:17.650
This was the thirty-eighth time he has
tried to illegally leave the country.

71
00:04:17.650 --> 00:04:20.530
And he returned in one piece?

72
00:04:20.530 --> 00:04:25.750
I suspect you are familiar with the details,
but allow me to briefly recount his life.

73
00:04:25.830 --> 00:04:28.790
<b>Kozuki Sukiyaki

Shogun of Wano
(Oden's Father)</b>

74
00:04:26.830 --> 00:04:28.790
Before he was even a year old,

75
00:04:29.330 --> 00:04:31.080
he sent his nanny flying.

76
00:04:31.080 --> 00:04:34.090
When he was two,
he caught two rabbits at once.

77
00:04:34.750 --> 00:04:38.550
At four, he hurled a boulder
at a bear and knocked it out.

78
00:04:38.970 --> 00:04:43.220
At age six, he spent all his time
frittering away the treasury at pleasure halls.

79
00:04:43.640 --> 00:04:47.020
When he was eight, 
he went alone to a gambling den

80
00:04:47.020 --> 00:04:51.730
and started a brawl with some
hot-tempered gamblers.

81
00:04:51.730 --> 00:04:54.440
When he was nine,
he was blacklisted by the yakuza.

82
00:04:55.070 --> 00:05:00.320
He repaid them by setting their
gambling den ablaze and starting a gang war.

83
00:05:00.320 --> 00:05:02.570
After that, he was arrested for assault.

84
00:05:02.990 --> 00:05:04.950
That was at the age of ten.

85
00:05:05.370 --> 00:05:10.370
He served time at the quarry,
which is when his skills blossomed.

86
00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:14.170
He climbed the ranks
and became a master stonemason!

87
00:05:14.590 --> 00:05:16.920
It must be his Kozuki blood!

88
00:05:18.510 --> 00:05:21.970
He returned to the streets a changed man!

89
00:05:22.550 --> 00:05:24.430
When Lord Oden was fourteen,

90
00:05:24.930 --> 00:05:26.470
a drought struck the capital.

91
00:05:27.180 --> 00:05:29.930
He could not just let people
suffer as the wells dried,

92
00:05:30.310 --> 00:05:34.060
so he changed the river's course
and made it flow to the capital.

93
00:05:36.190 --> 00:05:38.230
But it caused a massive flood...

94
00:05:38.860 --> 00:05:41.110
resulting in another arrest warrant!

95
00:05:42.450 --> 00:05:48.870
He attempted to flee from
the country through the channel...

96
00:05:50.710 --> 00:05:52.960
though he failed quite miserably!

97
00:05:53.750 --> 00:05:58.090
At fifteen, he strong-armed the master of
a mountain temple and stayed hidden there.

98
00:05:58.710 --> 00:06:04.890
He brought back women from the capital
every night and formed a harem!

99
00:06:06.800 --> 00:06:09.720
That makes him sound like
some kind of monster.

100
00:06:10.140 --> 00:06:15.100
I should add that all those women
were always free to leave.

101
00:06:15.560 --> 00:06:18.730
But there were some who could not abide this!

102
00:06:19.570 --> 00:06:23.740
They were those women's
boyfriends, parents, and husbands!

103
00:06:24.450 --> 00:06:26.950
A group of strapping samurai
accompanied them!

104
00:06:29.700 --> 00:06:34.210
Lord Oden welcomed
their challenge and fought back!

105
00:06:34.960 --> 00:06:37.920
This was known as the Harem War!

106
00:06:38.340 --> 00:06:45.180
The Hyogoro Family intervened to stop
them all, and a massive brawl took place!

107
00:06:45.180 --> 00:06:46.260
Enough!

108
00:06:48.850 --> 00:06:51.270
Lord Oden is now eighteen years old.

109
00:06:51.600 --> 00:06:53.730
He remains recalcitrant even now.

110
00:06:53.730 --> 00:06:56.150
That is all I have to report.

111
00:06:56.150 --> 00:07:00.270
Save your commentary
and deliver this to Oden.

112
00:06:56.930 --> 00:07:01.480
<b>Notice 
of
 Disownment</b>

113
00:07:05.030 --> 00:07:07.740
I've caught my lucky break.

114
00:07:07.740 --> 00:07:10.080
It's like winning the lottery.

115
00:07:10.660 --> 00:07:13.250
If I hand this over to the Kurokoma boss,

116
00:07:13.580 --> 00:07:15.710
I'll be set!

117
00:07:16.790 --> 00:07:17.830
Hey, you!

118
00:07:17.830 --> 00:07:19.960
Hand over your clothes!

119
00:07:25.760 --> 00:07:27.180
You won't get away this time!

120
00:07:27.180 --> 00:07:29.930
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa! Wait!

121
00:07:29.930 --> 00:07:32.890
I'm about to get so much money!

122
00:07:32.890 --> 00:07:34.390
You're full of it!

123
00:07:34.390 --> 00:07:38.020
It's true! Let me go to
the Kurokoma mansion!

124
00:07:39.230 --> 00:07:41.020
Kin'emon?

125
00:07:41.020 --> 00:07:44.530
Oh, that kid who stole our money?

126
00:07:45.070 --> 00:07:49.070
Catch him and flay him alive!

127
00:07:45.490 --> 00:07:51.330
<b>Hyogoro 
"the Flower"


Man of Chivalry, 
Flower Capital</b>

128
00:07:49.070 --> 00:07:51.330
But do not fight him one-on-one.

129
00:07:51.330 --> 00:07:55.080
He is stronger than you guys!

130
00:07:57.710 --> 00:08:00.080
I was entrusted with sixty silver!

131
00:08:00.080 --> 00:08:03.460
It'll be gone if I just spend it!

132
00:08:05.130 --> 00:08:07.010
Can I have the smaller pot?

133
00:08:07.000 --> 00:08:10.970
<b>30
Silver</b>
<b>60
Silver</b>

134
00:08:07.010 --> 00:08:09.430
I'm running an errand for someone.

135
00:08:09.430 --> 00:08:11.510
Sure! That'll be thirty silver!

136
00:08:10.970 --> 00:08:11.510
<b>30
Silver</b>
<b>60
Silver</b>

137
00:08:11.510 --> 00:08:12.510
'Kay.

138
00:08:12.510 --> 00:08:13.890
Thank you!

139
00:08:14.770 --> 00:08:16.980
Oh, I bought the wrong pot.

140
00:08:17.350 --> 00:08:19.520
I needed the bigger one.

141
00:08:20.650 --> 00:08:22.940
The bigger one is sixty silver.

142
